cs.DB, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.DS

This paper is about improving the security of databases outsourced to the cloud using hardware enclaves and oblivious query processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DB (Databases). The paper also discusses security and cryptography issues, which suggests the category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper proposes a new design for a database engine, which involves distributed computing, suggesting the category cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed system, which suggests the category cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper involves algorithms and data structures for efficient query processing, suggesting the category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
